<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Spells will trickle down to reasonable rates. heres why. there are only so many mages on the server. and possibility for infiinate spells.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If Uberguild_01 has 4 Mages, the guild will continue turning in Runes to receive 65 spells until all 4 Mages have these spells. Once everyone's spell lines are complete, Uberguild_01 will either 1) Save Runes for future members. 2) Give Runes to twinks 3) Start turning in Runes to spells that are &quot;precious&quot;.<br>
<br>
In regards to my point #3, Uberguild_01 would most likely turn the Runes into the Cleric, Shaman, and possibly Enchanter spell NPCs to obtain Group Virtue, Group Focus of Soul, or Voice of Quellious. Most likely, these spells will be highly sought after due to their tremendous functionality (for MGB) and will sell for extremely high prices.<br>
<br>
The above quoted statement would only be true if Runes were class specific such as Luclin-era spells. We already see the price for spells like Shock of Fiery Blades and Maelstrom of Electricity fall since they were introduced. Since Runes are not class-specific, Uberguild_01 has the choice of &quot;creating&quot; spells for whatever classes they choose.<br>
<br>
To get back to the point of the original poster, I do wish that 65 spells were more abundant. However, I don't agree with:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Casters are balanced off of there spells, yet alot dont have em.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->To take the Rogue example, when a Rogue levels to 65, the inherent power is only minimally increased (in terms of a higher minimum back-stab and maximum back-stab etc). When a Mage levels to 65, the damage dealt is also increased in terms of sustained DPS due to a larger mana-pool. With no introduction of new weapons and new spells, all things being equal, the power relationship would be approximately the same as Pre-PoP. However, added spells that increase the Mage's DPS would increase the relative power of the Mage in proportion to the Rogue if the Rogue did not receive a similar upgrade in the form of weapons. By making Runes as rare as a weapon upgrade, the risk vs. reward balance is maintained. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hukt2>hukt2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#333333>(1/10/03 10:22:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1740.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Make ALL spells merchant bought.</span><hr size=1> Good point on the runes not class specific never thought of that before. One thing to remember also though is a mage's power is decided by both spells and equipment. It is the balance of the two where mellee is only equipment. SO a direct comparision saying spells are equal to mellee equipment is not true imo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarion81>Sarion81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(1/11/03 3:43:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1740.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Make ALL spells merchant bought.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Spells are NOT like gear is to melee's. A rogue isnt balanced off that ubar dagger in PoT. Casters are balanced off of there spells, yet alot dont have em.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This statement is really only relative to whichever expansion you are in.  In PoP, it seems like they have tried to make spells similar to getting gear.  For example, take our high end items, really only the elemental armor.  15% (avg. 7.5%) mana reduction to all spells, and 18% off cast times, 12.5% average mana off Sun Vortex, FT 8, a couple of spell slots saved.  Considering what we already have, while very nice, those items aren't going to compare the jump a monk would recieve from getting the staff from Sol Ro, and their elemental armor.  Their armor gives them castable Avatar (2sec cast, 100 atk +100 to melee stats), and 150atk from their other slots (plus some hp regen).  Add our spells, and then you've got pretty even upgrades.  This is why I think that spectrals and Runes are really only available in teir 3 and up.  You can get them lower, but very very rare.  If anything, we should be glad that our spells will one day be sold in the bazaar, because that staff never will be, neither will the 17/19 peircer rogues get.  We should also be glad that the water pet is level 62, considering the damage upgrade, level 65 would be more appropriate.  Guess we lucked out there.<br>
<br>
As for selling spells, I think you guys are thinking too narrowly.  Not only guilds are going to be getting them.  Most of the runes my guild has came from exp groups.  Once most people have their spells spectrals and runes will be randomed on as money loot.  The smart person would attempt to get whatever there is a lack of in the market.  If everyone is trying to sell C5, I'm sure as hell not gonna try for an enchanter spell, I'm gonna try and get a good wizard or mage spell.  That way the spell will actually sell.  Also, you get extras before the class is done with that level of spell.  For example, all the mages in my guild have Black Steel, Malosinia, Jewelry Bag, Maelstrom of Thunder, and Shield of Maelin.  We still need:<br>
<br>
1 Blade of Kedge<br>
1 Child of Ro (laugh)<br>
1 Maelstrom of Ro<br>
1 planar renewal<br>
2 elemental silences<br>
4 girdle of Magi'Kot<br>
5 destroy summon<br>
<br>
Its going to take a lot of turn ins to get 5 destroy summons, and 4 girdles.  All the duplicates we get are gonna get sold, and until all our mages have their 63-64 spells, I'm gonna keep rolling for them, and keep selling the extras.  In fact we've already been selling copies of Black Steel, Maelstrom of Thunder and Jewelry Bag.  Similar things will happen with runes.  3/5 mages in my guild already have Sun Vortex, only 1/5 has earth pet and charm (damn you Cydmab! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).  We'll probably get several duplicates that the guild doesn't need before all our mages have all their 65 spells.  Add to that that there are 3-4 other guilds capable of getting spectrals and runes on my server, I'm pretty sure they'll start reaching the market really soon.  Well, spectrals already have, I mean rune spells will hit the market soon. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29130">Master Sarion Ifrinteine</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
